that is a pretty nice rod, sorry to hear you are departing with it.  I have looked on Ebay for fly rods, mainly older rods that are no longer made, and have come to the conclusion that folks are always looking for what is not offered, and when something they are looking for is offered, they either don't want to pay 65% of retail or decide they don't really want it.  I imagine the rod would sell for the amount you want, but not on Ebay.   Scott rods are not like Sage or Orvis rods when it comes to resale values.  Scott rods are more of a cult rod, especially the G series.  The advice John gave you is right on the mark.   Whomever buys you rod will be a lucky fly fisher<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
